s been given a series order by [[HBO]].<ref name=\"order\">{{cite news|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title='Mrs. Fletcher': HBO Picks Up Comedy Pilot Starring Kathryn Hahn To Series|url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/mrs-fletcher-hbo-comedy-series-kathryn-hahn-star-pickup-1202449437/|accessdate=August 21, 2018|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=August 21, 2018}}</ref> The pilot was written by Perrotta and directed by [[Nicole Holofcener]].<ref name=\"order\"/>\n\nOn August 16, 2019, it was announced that the series would premiere on October 27, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=Video: \"Mrs. Fletcher\" - Official Teaser - HBO|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/video/2019/06/28/video-mrs-fletcher-official-teaser-hbo-281403/20190628hbo03/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=June 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Limited Series \"Mrs. Fletcher\" Debuts October 27; Created by Executive Producer and Writer Tom Perrotta|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/08/16/limited-series-mrs-fletcher-debuts-october-27-created-by-executive-producer-and-writer-tom-perrotta-113113/20190816hbo01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=August 16, 2019}}</ref> In advance of its broadcast premiere, several episodes of the series received a preview screening in the Primetime program of the [[2019 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref>Debra Yeo, [https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/tiff/2019/09/06/think-programming-more-than-300-tiff-movies-is-hard-try-filling-just-six-tv-slots.html \"Think programming more than 300 TIFF movies is hard? Try filling just six TV slots\"]. ''[[Toronto Star]]'', September 6, 2019.</ref>\n\n==Premise==\n''Mrs. Fletcher'' is a coming of age story of Mrs. Eve Fletcher (Hahn) and her son Brendan (White).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/2019/07/02/first-look-hbo-mrs-fletcher-teases-kathryn-hahn-sexual-awakening/0lz2UXLVUmAilNWOwFkjWM/story.html|title=First look at HBO's 'Mrs. Fletcher' teases Kathryn Hahn's 'sexual awakening' - The Boston Globe|last=Isaac|first=Feldberg|date=July 2, 2019|website=BostonGlobe.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-19}}</ref> Eve is a divorc\u00e9e and is undergoing a mid-life crisis. She decides she no longer wants to be her old self<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.criticalhit.net/entertainment/kathryn-hahn-doesnt-want-to-be-a-good-girl-anymore-in-this-trailer-for-hbos-mrs-fletcher/|title=Kathryn Hahn doesn't want to be a good girl anymore in this trailer for HBO's Mrs Fletcher|last=Risi|first=Craig|date=2019-07-03|website=Critical Hit|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-07-19}}</ref> when her son Brendan goes to college as a freshman.<ref name=\":0\"/> She experiences sexual reawakening and sexual fulfillment that eluded her in her younger years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/mrs-fletcher-trailer/|title='Mrs. Fletcher' Trailer: Kathryn Hahn Gets Her Groove Back|last=Hoai-Tran|first=Bui|date=2019-07-03|website=/Film|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-19}}</ref> Brendan also undergoes his own sexual troubles as he navigates college life.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n===Main===\n* [[Kathryn Hahn]] as Eve Fletcher ([[n\u00e9e]] Mackie)<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite news|last1=Canfield|first1=David|title=Kathryn Hahn HBO comedy 'Mrs. Fletcher' picked up to series|url=https://ew.com/tv/2018/08/21/kathryn-hahn-mrs-fletcher-hbo-series/|accessdate=August 21, 2018|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=August 21, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n* Jackson White as Brendan Fletcher, Eve's son<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n* [[Owen Teague]] as Julian, Brendan's high school classmate, later a classmate in Eve's creative writing course<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n* [[Cameron Boyce]] as Zach, Brendan's college roommate<ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title='Descendants' Star Cameron Boyce Joins HBO Comedy Series 'Mrs. Fletcher'|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/descendants-cameron-boyce-hbo-comedy-series-mrs-fletcher-kathryn-hahn-1202533977/|website=Deadline|accessdate=January 19, 2019|date=January 17, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Domenick Lombardozzi]] as George, Roy's son<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/mrs-fletcher-domenick-lombardozzi-to-co-star-in-hbo-comedy-series-1202547396/|title='Mrs. Fletcher': Domenick Lombardozzi To Co-Star In HBO Comedy Series|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=February 1, 2019|accessdate=February 1, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Jen Richards]] as Margo, a [[transgender]] woman who teaches a creative writing course Eve enrolls in<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n* If\u00e1dansi Rashad as Curtis, a classmate in Eve's creating writing course\n* Katie Kershaw as Amanda Olney, Eve's coworker and friend<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[Casey Wilson]] as Jane, Eve's close friend<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n* [[Jasmine Cephas Jones]] as Chloe<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/mrs-fletcher-jasmine-cephas-jones-recur-hbo-comedy-series-kathryn-hahn-1202541597/|title='Mrs. Fletcher': Jasmine Cephas Jones To Recur On HBO Comedy Series|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=January 25, 2019|accessdate=February 1, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Bill Raymond]] as Roy Rafferty\n* [[Josh Hamilton (actor)|Josh Hamilton]] as Ted Fletcher, Eve's ex-husband and Brendan's father\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table|background=#5B3256 |overall= |title= |titleR=<ref name=\"episodes\">{{cite news |title=Limited Series MRS. FLETCHER Debuts October 27; Created by Executive Producer and Writer Tom Perrotta |url=https://medium.com/hbo-cinemax-pr/mrs-fletcher-debuts-october-27-on-hbo-dda88fc99ab0 |accessdate=September 18, 2019 |work=[[HBO]] |date=September 16, 2019 |language=en}}</ref> |director= |directorR=<ref name=\"episodes\"/> |writer= |writerR=<ref name=\"episodes\"/> |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=\"episodes\"/> |country=U.S.|viewers=|episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 1\n |Title = Empty Best\n |DirectedBy = [[Nicole Holofcener]]\n |WrittenBy = [[Tom Perrotta]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|27}}\n |Viewers = 0.312<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-sunday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-27-2019.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Sunday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 10.27.2019|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=October 29, 2019|work=[[Showbuzz Daily]]|accessdate=October 29, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = {{Plot|episode|date=November 2019}}Single mother and divorcee Eve Fletcher works at an assisted living facility. One resident, Ray, is caught watching porn in front of other residents, and his son George balks at Eve's suggestion that Ray should move to a different facility. At home, Eve prepares for her only child, Brendan, to leave for college the next day. Brendan cuts their last dinner at home together short to attend a party with his friends. There, Brendan talks with Becca, a girl he had sex with then [[Ghosting (relationships)|ghosted]], and bullies classmate Julian. Eve is discouraged to learn that her ex-husband Ted will not be able to help move Brendan in the next day. Her friend Jane comes over to commiserate about their children moving away and encourages her to open up to new experiences. That night, Brendan [[sexting|sends a picture of his penis]] to Becca, which prompts her to visit him the next day. Eve is horrified to overhear Brendan using derogatory language to Becca while she performs oral sex on him, and uncomfortably attempts to broach the subject of respecting women on their drive to college. After Eve unpacks Brendan's things, she wishes to stay, but he escorts her out. Back at home, Eve begins adjusting to living alone. In bed that night, she [[Google (verb)|Googles]] \"MILF\" - a term her friend Jane earlier used to compliment her - and watches a pornographic video from the search results out of curiosity. Later, Eve arrives at a local community college for a creative writing course and meets Julian, who is one of her classmates.\n |LineColor = 5B3256\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 2\n |T